Sentencas: This study investigates the impact of zinc oxide on the physical characteristics and electrochemical behavior of the LaSrCoFe (LSCF) cathode.
Titulo: Influence of ZnO on Electrochemical and Physiochemical Properties of Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite as Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectra in conjunction with the bode phase were used to optimize the amount of zinc oxide addition in the LSCF cathode.
Titulo: Influence of ZnO on Electrochemical and Physiochemical Properties of Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite as Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Brunauer-Emmett-Teller (BET) and thermal analysis were utilized to substantiate the electrochemical discovery that the LSCF: ZnO ratio yields rational oxygen reduction reaction and stoichiometric outcomes.
Titulo: Influence of ZnO on Electrochemical and Physiochemical Properties of Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite as Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Initial characterization, comprising of phase and bonding analyses, indicated that LSCF-ZnO was successfully synthesized at 800 degrees C using an improved modified sol-gel technique.
Titulo: Influence of ZnO on Electrochemical and Physiochemical Properties of Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite as Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The addition of 5% zinc oxide to LSCF results in the lowest overall area-specific resistance (ASR) rating.
Titulo: Influence of ZnO on Electrochemical and Physiochemical Properties of Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite as Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The Bode phase implies that the addition of 5% zinc oxide to LSCF reduces the low-frequency impedance by 64.28%, indicating that the cathode experienced a greater oxygen reduction reaction.
Titulo: Influence of ZnO on Electrochemical and Physiochemical Properties of Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite as Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: After the addition of 5% zinc oxide, a single LSCF-ZnO cell may function at temperatures as low as 650 degrees C, and the LSCF cathode power density is increased by 25.35%.
Titulo: Influence of ZnO on Electrochemical and Physiochemical Properties of Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite as Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The surface morphology of the LSCF-ZnO cathode reveals an overall particle size of less than 100 nm, and mapping analysis reveals a homogeneous distribution of ZnO over the cathode layer.
Titulo: Influence of ZnO on Electrochemical and Physiochemical Properties of Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite as Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Consequently, LSCF-ZnO demonstrated outstanding chemical compatibility between LSCF and ZnO, bonding characteristics, and electrochemical performance with the capacity to function at an intermediate temperature (600 degrees C - 800 degrees C).
Titulo: Influence of ZnO on Electrochemical and Physiochemical Properties of Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite as Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
